3. cs.RO (Robotics) - Planning problems are also relevant to robotics, and the paper mentions the use of MCTS in robotics applications. 
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - While not the main focus of the paper, the Sokoban problem involves visual perception and manipulation, which could be relevant to computer vision. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper proposes a neural network architecture and uses backpropagation to train it, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
